1
00:00:02,686 --> 00:00:06,981
We need to be very cautious
about these kind of things;

2
00:00:06,981 --> 00:00:09,971
because what is it that 
we are ourselves,

3
00:00:09,971 --> 00:00:14,261
understand first of all,

4
00:00:14,261 --> 00:00:17,256
before we’re exporting 
that to others.

5
00:00:17,749 --> 00:00:22,359
[Concentrate on Yourself]

6
00:00:22,740 --> 00:00:28,141
Guru Mahārāj would quote 
different maxims.

7
00:00:28,151 --> 00:00:30,230
Some of them come to mind,

8
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:32,710
and I don’t mean 
to be harsh or cruel,

9
00:00:32,710 --> 00:00:40,462
but just to sort of invoke
his divine concepts first

10
00:00:40,462 --> 00:00:42,612
and then work from there.

11
00:00:42,612 --> 00:00:47,211
And one thing he said 
many times was,

12
00:00:47,461 --> 00:00:50,111
“Oil your own machine.”

13
00:00:50,961 --> 00:00:54,406
Again, that’s he didn’t 
create that statement.

14
00:00:54,406 --> 00:00:59,026
He is quoting an aphorism.
“Oil your own machine”

15
00:00:59,026 --> 00:01:02,262
means concentrate on yourself.

16
00:01:02,432 --> 00:01:07,017
Many times he liked to quote
this German scholar,

17
00:01:07,017 --> 00:01:12,467
who read Bhagavad-gītā,
and came to the conclusion

18
00:01:12,467 --> 00:01:16,009
that the message 
of Bhagavad-gītā is

19
00:01:16,009 --> 00:01:20,499
‘not to quarrel 
with the environment’.

20
00:01:20,499 --> 00:01:22,558
Like we hear things 
early on …

21
00:01:22,558 --> 00:01:26,878
Just one sample of that 
would be the famous śloka,

22
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:31,125
mātrā-sparśās tu kaunteya
śītoṣṇa-sukha-duḥkha-dāḥ
 

23
00:01:31,125 --> 00:01:36,145
āgamāpāyino ’nityās
tāṁs titikṣasva bhārata
[Bg: 2.14]

24
00:01:36,145 --> 00:01:38,786
Where Kṛṣṇa is comparing

25
00:01:38,786 --> 00:01:46,146
karmic circumstances 
to environmental conditions—

26
00:01:46,146 --> 00:01:50,441
seasonal changes, 
temperatures.

27
00:01:50,867 --> 00:01:53,747
And what I like to say 
as a footnote,

28
00:01:53,747 --> 00:01:57,966
that even as devotees or 
those somewhat familiar

29
00:01:57,966 --> 00:02:02,177
with what’s presented 
in Bhagavad-gītā,

30
00:02:02,177 --> 00:02:03,317
we can think,

31
00:02:03,317 --> 00:02:06,757
’Oh, we’ve heard that, 
we know that.

32
00:02:07,037 --> 00:02:10,961
That’s in the second chapter,
we’ve heard that many times.’

33
00:02:11,031 --> 00:02:16,121
But what I would remind
even the devotees of …

34
00:02:18,421 --> 00:02:23,189
if Kṛṣṇa gives
a particular example,

35
00:02:23,189 --> 00:02:26,359
we can assume
it’s a very good one.

36
00:02:26,359 --> 00:02:29,249
[Laughing]

37
00:02:29,249 --> 00:02:30,569
It’s not like 
He’s saying,

38
00:02:30,569 --> 00:02:32,719
“Oh, I should have said …”,
or

39
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:34,859
“Why didn’t I think of that?”

40
00:02:35,719 --> 00:02:36,849
He, Who’s ...

41
00:02:36,849 --> 00:02:38,518
We hear 
in other places,

42
00:02:38,518 --> 00:02:41,648
upadraṣṭānumantā ca
bhartā bhoktā maheśvaraḥ
 

43
00:02:41,648 --> 00:02:44,788
paramātmeti cāpy ukto
dehe ’smin puruṣaḥ paraḥ
[Bg: 13.23]

44
00:02:44,788 --> 00:02:46,808
He is as the Paramātmā
in everyone.

45
00:02:46,808 --> 00:02:47,998
So, I would think,

46
00:02:47,998 --> 00:02:50,618
if He’s going 
to give an example,

47
00:02:50,618 --> 00:02:53,541
it must be 
a really good one.

48
00:02:54,101 --> 00:02:57,820
He has an idea 
of what would be

49
00:02:57,820 --> 00:03:03,200
an example that most 
simple‒hearted people

50
00:03:04,380 --> 00:03:08,128
could find tenable
or acceptable.

51
00:03:08,628 --> 00:03:11,988
And I’m saying 
this indirectly, that …

52
00:03:11,988 --> 00:03:13,148
I guess I’m saying,

53
00:03:13,148 --> 00:03:16,780
it’s Kṛṣṇa’s job
to do that.

54
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:20,400
And He does His job 
very well.

55
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:24,141
Although He … 
we can say,

56
00:03:24,161 --> 00:03:28,541
He’s passive in this context, 
or non-interfering,

57
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:34,151
but still: conscience,
inner suggestion—

58
00:03:34,151 --> 00:03:35,961
all of these things 
are there.

59
00:03:35,961 --> 00:03:39,370
We all know, by our own
practical experience

60
00:03:39,370 --> 00:03:41,010
in life, in living,

61
00:03:41,010 --> 00:03:46,611
everyone has an inner 
dialogue that’s going on.

62
00:03:47,151 --> 00:03:51,334
It’s a sort of a dialogue 
with the self.

63
00:03:51,334 --> 00:03:54,504
A dialogue with ourselves, 
you could call it.

64
00:03:54,504 --> 00:03:56,358
All day …

65
00:03:56,358 --> 00:04:01,298
In fact, it would be 
more rare, the moments,

66
00:04:01,298 --> 00:04:04,378
when that dialogue 
is not obvious.

67
00:04:04,658 --> 00:04:06,838
But there’s …
People are always …

68
00:04:06,838 --> 00:04:08,229
There is a voice …

69
00:04:08,229 --> 00:04:10,639
You’re talking 
to yourself inside.

70
00:04:10,639 --> 00:04:14,779
Making observations 
about life, circumstances,

71
00:04:14,779 --> 00:04:17,565
from many different perspective.

72
00:04:17,565 --> 00:04:25,056
So, within that the suggestion 
is also coming,

73
00:04:25,056 --> 00:04:27,584
what we 
can call conscience

74
00:04:27,584 --> 00:04:29,104
from a plane
‘how to proceed’,

75
00:04:29,104 --> 00:04:32,004
‘what’s right’,
‘what’s wrong’.

76
00:04:32,539 --> 00:04:39,759
But referring back to that śloka,
which ends on this expression,

77
00:04:39,759 --> 00:04:42,504
tāṁs titikṣasva bhārata
[Bg: 2.14]—

78
00:04:43,664 --> 00:04:44,608
what do you do 
in the world

79
00:04:44,608 --> 00:04:48,401
with seasonal changes, 
environmental conditions?
 

80
00:04:48,401 --> 00:04:50,451
—You tolerate it.

81
00:04:50,451 --> 00:04:54,291
Right now we have the AC on,
because it’s hot here.

82
00:04:54,291 --> 00:04:57,202
You make some adjustment,
but basically,

83
00:04:57,202 --> 00:05:00,091
you have to tolerate 
these conditions.

84
00:05:00,091 --> 00:05:02,444
So, that’s 
what’s indicated there.

85
00:05:02,444 --> 00:05:03,514
Guru Mahārāj is saying,

86
00:05:03,514 --> 00:05:09,667
“That scholar’s
summary interpretation—

87
00:05:09,779 --> 00:05:12,262
and again,
it was an observation.

88
00:05:12,262 --> 00:05:16,112
His summary observation was,
“Oh, the message is

89
00:05:16,112 --> 00:05:19,487
‘don’t quarrel 
with the environment’.”

90
00:05:20,104 --> 00:05:26,323
But you can
adjust yourself.

91
00:05:27,923 --> 00:05:31,663
And, so, that’s back to
“Oil your own machine.”

